install [python extension](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemname=ms-python.python) - install [pylance extension](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemname=ms-python.vscode-pylance) - set `pylance` as your python language server - install `boto3-stubs[kafka]` in your environment: ```bash python -m pip install 'boto3-stubs[kafka]' ``` both type checking and code completion should now work. no explicit type annotations required, write your `boto3` code as usual. ### pycharm install `boto3-stubs-lite[kafka]` in your environment: ```bash python -m pip install 'boto3-stubs-lite[kafka]'` ``` both type checking and code completion should now work. explicit type annotations **are required**. use `boto3-stubs` package instead for implicit type discovery. ### emacs - mypy_boto3_kafka.type_defs import amazonmskclustertypedef def get_value() -> amazonmskclustertypedef: return {...} ``` ## how it works fully automated [mypy-boto3-builder](https://github.com/youtype/mypy_boto3_builder) carefully generates type annotations for each service, patiently waiting for `boto3` updates. it delivers drop-in type annotations for you and makes sure that: - all available `boto3` services are covered. - each public class and method of every `boto3` service gets valid type annotations extracted from `botocore` schemas. - type annotations include up-to-date documentation. - link to documentation is provided for every method. - code is processed by [black](https://github.com/psf/black) and [isort](https://github.com/pycqa/isort) for readability. ## what's new ### implemented features - fully type annotated `boto3`, `botocore`, `aiobotocore` and `aioboto3` libraries - `mypy`, `pyright`, `vscode`, `pycharm`, `sublime text` and `emacs` compatibility - `client`, `serviceresource`, `resource`, `waiter` `paginator` type annotations for each service - generated `typedefs` for each service - generated `literals` for each service - auto discovery of types for `boto3.client` and `boto3.resource` calls - auto discovery of types for `session.client` and `session.resource` calls - auto discovery of types for `client.get_waiter` and `client.get_paginator` calls - auto discovery of types for `serviceresource` and `resource` collections - auto discovery of types for `aiobotocore.session.create_client` calls ### latest changes builder changelog can be found in [releases](https://github.com/youtype/mypy_boto3_builder/releases). ## versioning `mypy-boto3-kafka` documentation_summary: The HTML text is a PyPI (Python Package Index) page for the package `mypy-boto3-kafka` version 1.34.0, released on December 13, 2023. This package provides type annotations for the `boto3.Kafka` service, generated with `mypy-boto3-builder` version 7.21.0, to enhance code quality and developer productivity by enabling better autocomplete and error detection in IDEs. It supports Python versions 3.7 and above and is compatible with various IDEs like VSCode, PyCharm, Emacs, and Sublime Text. The package, licensed under the MIT License, is developed by Vlad Emelianov and aims at developers working with AWS Kafka service in Python, offering features like client annotations, paginator annotations, literals, and type definitions for improved type checking and code completion.
